  "body": "As always, the tricky part of this is when the remote network is running a different hardfork than the local one. Here's a description of the different cases:\r\n\r\n- London Hardhat forking a London Network\r\n    - Same behavior as a local network with London, except remote blocks before the hardfork don't have the `baseFeePerGas` field.\r\n    - The base fee is respected. That is, the first local block after forking has the correct base `baseFeePerGas`\r\n- Non-London Hardhat forking a Non-London network\r\n    - Same behavior as a local network using a pre-London hardfork.\r\n- Non-London Hardhat forking a London network\r\n    - New blocks, or remote blocks before the hardfork don't have the `baseFeePerGas`. EIP-1559 transactions are not accepted.\r\n- London Hardhat forking a Non-London Network\r\n    - New blocks have the London behavior. The initial base fee is the configured one.",
